The article is a statement by the President of the United States on the situation in Syria. The President condemns the use of force by the Syrian government against demonstrators and calls for it to end immediately. The statement expresses regret for the loss of life and offers condolences to the families of the victims. The President criticizes the Syrian government for not taking meaningful steps towards reform and for refusing to respect the rights of the Syrian people. The article also mentions that the Syrian government has blamed outsiders and sought assistance from Iran to suppress its citizens. The United States strongly opposes the Syrian government's treatment of its citizens and its support for terrorism. The President reaffirms the commitment of the United States to democracy and universal human rights.